\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {Sometimes when I think of being stopped at the border I think of the checkpoints the Americans would set up in Iraq.  In the chaos of that war they would divide up that country an separate families from each other.\line \line Sometimes these checkpoints were difficult to make out given the language barrier and the rush of it all.  Families. Whole familes would turn a corner and come upon these barricades only to be met by jumpy soldiers with powerful rounds who would turn their cannons on these cars. Families, whole families of fathers, mothers and children of all ages died in these moments. Again and again.}
\par\plain {And these men and women came home. They were called brave, they were called heroes and thanked for their service.  }
\par\plain {These are your neighbours.}}